title: Data Analyst (Resource Development)
description:
Job Summary

Provides advanced technical support to engineers in the Resource Development department. Performs routine and complex activities involving data acquisition, data management, report generation, analytics, and information processing. Continually strives to implement automation and to streamline processes...

Performs a wide variety of tasks; contributes to process improvements. Acts as a resource for team members with less experience. Thorough working knowledge of technical/specialized tasks and responsibilities. Relies on experience and exercises independent judgment to determine best approach to achieve desired outcomes. Works under general supervision.

Duties And Responsibilities
• Accumulate and effectively organize engineering data from multiple sources for engineering analysis.
• Develops, implements, and maintains standardized technical and engineering staff processes.
• Considered the go-to resource for well data analysis; discovers and troubleshoots data issues across sources and drives issues to resolution.
• Works independently to perform more complex data analyses.
• Confirm accuracy of well and production data, take appropriate action on any changes, and communicate required corrections to the necessary parties.
• Create and maintain custom database(s) and spreadsheets of technical data as required by group.
• Responsible for verifying, manipulating, analyzing, creating, automating, and reporting data.
• Demonstrates a thorough working knowledge of technology, applications, terminology, and procedures required of the job function.
• Monitors new technologies and draws upon expertise to make recommendations for further exploitation of existing technologies.
• Provides advanced user support for software systems to other technical support and professional personnel, including troubleshooting user problems.
• Participates in training and sharing knowledge across the team, department, and company.
• Executes data & analytics tasks from beginning to end with minimal supervision in order to streamline processes and generate data driven insights for the team and across the company; may require oversight for more advanced technical workflows.
• Collaborates with varying levels of engineers and management to generate and deliver high-quality datasets, dashboards, visualizations, and tools to support engineering workflows, data quality efforts and data analytics.
• Knowledge of E&P operations and/or desire to learn more about the core business.
• Personal commitment to inclusion and diversity.
• Other duties as assigned.

Skills And Competencies
• Strong communication skills, both written and oral.
• Proficient computer skills.
• Self-starter, with ability to work as part of a team or individually to perform more complex data analyses.
• Desire to improve and streamline tools used widely by the company.
• Flexible and able to handle multiple tasks at one time.
• Ability to work and deliver on short timelines.
• Close attention to detail.
• Ability to process large amounts of data to generate executive-level quality presentations.
• Action oriented - Taking on new opportunities and tough challenges with a sense of urgency, high energy, and enthusiasm.
• Instills trust - Gaining the confidence and trust of others through honesty, integrity, and authenticity.
• Ensures accountability - Holding self and others accountable to meet commitments.
• Drives results - Consistently achieving results, even under tough circumstances.
• Nimble learning - Actively learning through experimentation when tackling new problems, using both successes and failures as learning fodder.

Required Qualifications
• High school diploma or general education degree (GED).
• 3+ years of closely related industry experience.
• Experience with databases and data structure.
• Experience working in Aries or a reserves database.
• Advanced proficiency in MS Excel, MS Access, and SQL programming language.
• An acceptable pre-employment background and drug test.

Preferred Qualifications
• Bachelor’s degree from an accredited college or university in Business, Math, Computer Science, or related Science.
• At least a year serving an active role in data analytics projects.
• Proficiency in TIBCO Spotfire, including creation of tools and analysis using the application.
• Experience using GIS to perform advanced spatial mapping functions.

Physical Requirements And Working Conditions
• Requires prolonged sitting, some bending and stooping.
• Occasional lifting up to 25 pounds.
• Manual dexterity sufficient to operate a computer keyboard and calculator.

title: Sr. Data & Reporting Analyst
description:
Job Overview

Applied Systems, Inc., a worldwide leader in insurance technology, is currently searching for a Sr. Data & Reporting Analyst to join our Human Resources team. The Human Resources department is responsible for the development, administration, and delivery of business solutions and programs related to Applied’s Human Capital Strategy and people practices, including employee relations... policies, benefits, HRIS reporting, talent acquisition, performance management, and legal compliance.

The Sr. Data & Reporting Analyst will transform People data into reports and visuals that enable leaders to make informed, actionable decisions. This role will collaborate with internal and external partners to scope, build, and maintain systems integrations and play an integral role in ensuring people and employment data is accurate and secure.

What You'll Do
• Consult with relevant stakeholders to understand, define, and document business requirements for reporting, dashboards, and other data visualization needs; design, test, deploy, and maintain standard reports, dashboards, and scorecards.
• Monitor and analyze utilization of dashboards and reports; develop and execute plans to drive adoption, continuously improve relevancy to business, and decommission as appropriate.
• Identify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets.
• Design, test, deploy, and maintain Role-Based Permissions across systems, reports, dashboards, and scorecards.
• Create and implement protocols and procedures for auditing permissions and modifying data access at the Role- or User-level, and ensure data integrity by developing and executing necessary processes and controls around the flow of data.
• Perform data cleansing to ensure the accuracy and quality of data input and output across systems and analyze trends from data audits and cleansing to identify and recommend areas that require data, system, or process improvements.
• Coordinate cross-functional teams to document and define business requirements, recommend best-fit solution, and design, test, and deploy data transfer or application integrations.
• Lead data transfer and integration projects between HRIS and other internal or 3rd party providers.

What You’ll Need to Succeed

We’re looking for someone who:
• Ability to work 100% remotely, or from an Applied Systems office

Your experience should include some or all of the following:
• Minimum 5 years in data analysis, informatics, reporting, and data visualization
• Proven ability to manipulate and analyze high-volume, high-dimensionality data from varied sources
• Proficient in data visualization tools such as Power BI, Tableau, Looker, etc.
• Proficient in data transformation tools such as Alteryx, RStudio, RapidMiner, etc.
• Proficient in SQL; additional programming languages a plus
• Proficient with data transfer and Application Programming Interface (API) tools and methods
• Proficient in Microsoft 365, including Excel, PowerPoint, and Sharepoint
• Experience with UKG and iCIMS strongly preferred
• Experience with Atlassian tools such as Jira and Confluence a plus
• Strong communication and presentation skills
• Strong collaboration skills and ability to work effectively with all levels of internal/external stakeholders
• Bachelor’s degree in technology or related discipline, or equivalent combination of education and work experience
• We proudly support and encourage people with military experience, as well as military spouses, to apply

Additionally, you may have:
• Experience with UKG
• Experience with iCIMS

What You’ll Gain

Benefits from Day One
• Health insurance plans, dental, and vision
• Wellness incentives
• 401(k) and/or RRSP retirement savings plans with employer match

Work-Life Balance
• Competitive paid vacation time and a free day for your birthday
• Personal/sick time
• Paid holidays
• Flex Time

title: Senior Business Intelligence Analyst
description:
Job Overview

Applied Systems, Inc., a worldwide leader in insurance technology, is currently searching for a Senior Business Intelligence Data Analyst, in this role you will act as the day-to-day data analyst, manage data integrity and build effective, usable, well-designed reports, dashboards, and performance scorecards. You will deliver and drive insights to customer support with timely... accurate reports, helping to support data-driven operations productivity optimization, ensuring work is being handled equitably across teams, and maximizing the ability for Support to achieve business objectives.

What You’ll Do
• Day-to-day data analyst, manage data integrity and build effective, usable, well-designed reports, dashboards, and performance scorecards
• Create an end-to-end, robust reporting framework working closely with key stakeholders in Support
• Define KPIs, develop and maintain Support related metrics, dashboards, and scorecards in Salesforce & our future BI tool, in addition to ad hoc analysis to help drive business decisions
• Deliver and drive insights, helping to support data-driven operations optimization, productivity, and team enhancements, ensuring work is being handled equitably across teams
• Uncovers and corrects data fidelity issues, reconciles data discrepancies, and supports data governance initiatives
• Perform analytical deep dives to analyze ad-hoc data integrity issues & problems with very fast turnarounds
• Become an expert on key internal and external data sources.
• Work cross-functionally within the organization to identify opportunities to improve data quality and related data architecture practices
• Over time develop a strong understanding of Support strategy and leverage data insights to suggest operational improvements and measured outcomes
• Performs other duties as assigned by immediate manager or management team

What You’ll Need to Succeed

We’re looking for someone who:
• Can work remotely or from an Applied Systems office
• Ability to travel (post-COVID-19), Quarterly

Your experience should include some or all of the following:
• Two (2) to five (5) years of professional work experience in business analysis, reporting, strategy, analytics, business intelligence, or financial planning and reporting.
• Demonstrated performance and success in performance dashboard creation, mapping, and presenting data insights to various audiences preferably in a Customer Service or Operational capacity.
• Prior systems usage, including Salesforce object model (built & deployed Salesforce reports and dashboards)
• Intermediate/Advanced BI tool proficiency (Tableau, Power BI, Looker, etc.)
• Advanced proficiency in MS Excel, working with large datasets
• Motivated problem solver: high attention to detail, with the ability to troubleshoot complex or ambiguous problems while navigating conflicting priorities independently
• Present through business acumen: communicate (verbal & written) and translate business requirements into technical solutions to all levels of the organization
• Bachelor’s degree in finance, business, economics, mathematics, or other highly quantitative fields
• We proudly support and encourage people with military experience, as well as military spouses, to apply

Additionally, you may have:
• Prior experience in supporting strategic initiatives
• Worked in a Customer Support environment
• Worked in a Contact Center phone system environment
• Operations background

What You’ll Gain

Benefits from Day One
• Health insurance plans, dental, and vision
• Wellness incentives
• 401(k) and/or RRSP retirement savings plans with employer match

Work-Life Balance
• Competitive paid vacation time and a free day for your birthday
• Personal/sick time
• Paid holidays
• Flex Time
• Paid parental leave (U.S. candidates)
• Volunteer time off

title: Data Analyst Specialist - Programs Impact & Evaluation - Now Hiring
description:
Great benefits. Competitive pay. We know these are some of the things people look for in a job.

But if you're the kind of person who also cares about making an impact and serving our nation's wounded warriors and their families, then you're exactly the kind of person we're looking for. When you join Wounded Warrior Project, you're committing to making a difference. We make a commitment to you... too - helping you to find that spark, ignite your passion to serve, and embark on a career with meaning and purpose.

At Wounded Warrior Project we recognize our mission cannot be accomplished without our talented teammates, which is why we're proud to offer benefits such as:
• A flexible hybrid work schedule (3 days in office, 2 days' work from home)
• Full medical, dental and vision coverage for both teammates AND family members
• Competitive pay and performance incentives
• A fun, mission focused and collaborative team environment

A mission that matters is just the beginning, so if you're ready to get started, we're ready for you.
The Wounded Warrior Project (WWP) Mission Data & Insights Data Analytics team investigates matters of interests to program leadership in a systematic manner to synthesize and communicate data-derived knowledge, increasing collective understanding of WWP program effectiveness across all services to promote the well-being of warriors and their families and expand awareness of the post-9/11 veteran population.

DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES
• Systematically process large dataset, including but not limited to data processing (data cleaning, transformation, summarization, and analysis). This includes implementing best practices and other appropriate quality assurance procedures to inspect the data for accuracy and quality (such as the presence of outliers, missing data, patterns in missing, nonsensical values etc.).
• Transform qualitative and quantitative data, from both structured and unstructured sources for analysis.
• Develop and maintain consistent and accurate process documentation in coordination with the Data Analytics team that contributes to the collective systematic approach for planning, collecting, processing, and analyzing data to facilitate consistency, repeatability, and efficiency.
• Build and maintain productive and collaborative business relationships with stakeholders across the organization and serve as trusted partner to program teams to ensure a warrior-centric philosophy is demonstrated throughout.
• Lead reporting and analytics prepared by the impact evaluation team. Ensure rigor, accuracy, and consistency of analytic methods and data reporting. Perform quality assurance checks on all data-related deliverables to ensure accuracy and validity.
• Apply methods of storytelling with data to communicate intent or need that aims to inform program direction for warrior programs and services. This includes preparing non-technical summaries of findings and recommendations that are easily understood and used by lay audiences.
• Interpret complex data and generate data driven insights in a clear, effective, and concise manner, leveraging the use of data visualizations that target broad audiences that are both technical and non-technical consumers of information.
• Collaborate with Impact Evaluation team and Warrior Research teams to identify relevant data points to communicate to external audiences for marketing materials, executive speaking engagements, and other external facing events to accurately and effectively communicate key points obtained through analysis.
• Coordinate data sharing at scale, e.g., via meetings, print and digital materials, for a variety of audiences. Inform business decisions and communicate data clearly. Collaborate with marketing and program leadership as needed.
• Identify and recommend opportunities for strategies, tactics, and tools to generate efficiency and consistency.
• Work collaboratively with internal and external teams to meet organizational objectives and share learnings and best practices.
• Other related duties as assigned.

KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, & ABILITIES
• Strong analytical skills. Demonstrated ability to identify problems, analyze information, evaluate results, and solve problems using the most effective solutions.
• Strong organizational and time management skills. Demonstrated ability to adapt to changing priorities and meet deadlines and deliverables under tight time constraints.
• Strong written and verbal communication skills. Demonstrated ability to effectively communicate with stakeholders, ask critical questions, and obtain pertinent information and details. Demonstrated ability to effectively interpret and explain complex information. Demonstrated ability to anticipate questions and areas of concern and provide solid responses for leadership.
• Strong documentation skills. Demonstrated attention to detail and accuracy.
• Working understanding of best practices to collect, store, manage, share, and use data to inform strategy implementation.
• Demonstrated working understanding of data analytics and reporting, and statistical testing using statistical software to support the team and the work.
• Demonstrated ability to think creatively and innovatively, based on continuous learning and understanding of technology and trends, and share to take the Impact Evaluation team to the next level. Demonstrated inquisitiveness and listening skills to understand the 'why' behind trends and changes.
• High energy level. Self- starter: willing to take initiative and collaborate with teammates to work effectively.
• Unequivocal commitment to the highest standards of personal and business ethics and conduct.
• Mission-driven, guided by core values, and a pleasure to work with.

EXPERIENCE

Requirements
• Two years of experience working with data, analytics, interpreting complex data, or reporting data for decision-making.
• Two years of experience sharing data via meetings, print and digital materials, and communicating data results to executive leadership.

Preferences
• Three years of experience in a non-profit environment or working with military or veteran organizations.
• Two years of experience applying analytical methods and familiarity with regression analysis and modeling.
• Three years of experience performing statistical tests on data sets using STATA, SAS, R, or other statistical software.

EDUCATION

Requirements
• Bachelor's degree. Equivalent combination of education, experience, training, and certification may be considered in lieu of degree.

Preferences
• Master's degree in informatics, data analytics, business, accounting, economics, finance, or comparable program.

CERTIFICATIONS & LICENSURE

Requirements
• None.

Preferences
• None.

WORK ENVIRONMENT/PHYSICAL DEMANDS
• General office environment; temperature controlled.
• Up to 25% travel.

We recognize the success of our mission depends on the efforts of our passionate, hard-working teammates. To help teammates remain focused on the warriors and families we serve, WWP offers a comprehensive benefits package that includes: Medical/Prescription drug, Dental, Vision, Life/AD&D, Short-term Disability, Long-term Disability, and an Employee Assistance Program. WWP also offers a 401(k) retirement plan, a competitive PTO package, Sick Leave, Family Care Leave, Paid Holidays, Birthday Holiday, Education Assistance, and Bereavement Leave.

For Colorado Applicants: The estimated hiring range for this position is between $51,200 - $76,800 annual base salary,subject to a candidate's combination of experience, qualifications, and credentials. This position may also be eligible for an annual performance incentive.

For New York Applicants:The estimated hiring range for this position is between $58,880 - $88,320 annual base salary,subject to a candidate's combination of experience, qualifications, and credentials. This position may also be eligible for an annual performance incentive.

title: Sr Technical Data Analyst
description:
Job Description:
This position focuses the majority of their time producing analytical solutions (reports, dashboards, tools, etc.) for leadership and stakeholders across the organization that supports business or clinical initiatives. This position provides consultation and support in the development, analysis, interpretation, and management of a variety of highly complex data sources to support... process improvement, operations, strategy, cost reduction, and increased patient safety and satisfaction.
_Position is 100% remote, however, currently we are unable to consider candidates for remote opportunities in the following states: California, Hawaii, New Jersey, New York, and Washington._
This position is responsible for providing analytical support - typically at a system-wide level. May work as part of a system-wide team or interact with stakeholders across the system. Typically this position performs analysis on highly complex projects under general supervision. This position works with data sources serving the needs of customers in one or more business areas:
Institute for Healthcare Delivery Research / Clinical Programs: Provides consultative assistance to physicians and administrators from internal and external health care systems who are attending training in health care quality improvement. Acts as content expert for data related to the clinical area assigned. Supports clinical development teams in reporting, research, data exploration, and care process development and tracking.
Core Essentials:
1. Creates reports that answer multiple related questions as well as reports with linked content, drilldown, and nested parameters. The report is formatted in such a way that leads the user through the report in a well-organized, easy to understand fashion.
2. Writes more advanced SQL including some query tuning and complex joins (e.g., outer joins on multiple tables). Uses sub-queries and the With Statement as well as more complex functions (e.g., Substr, To_Date, date calculations, etc.).
3. Assists in the identification of data quality (accuracy, completeness, etc.) issues. Assists with the process of database design for assigned projects. As appropriate, trains other individuals and teams in the routine use of data collection, analysis, and reporting and interpretation tools for measuring performance.
4. Demonstrates an understanding of Primary / Foreign Keys, Table / Field Aliases, and Partitions / Indexes to produce high quality material.
5. Provides project management / project leadership as appropriate to drive timelines and deliverables.
6. Trains others on skills and competencies required for previous levels of Data Analyst.
Additional Essentials:
1. Collaborates with corporate and region resources to design, create, test, and implement analytic tools (databases, reports, web applications, dashboards, etc.) that support enterprise / region needs and to improve data collection and reporting strategies (minimize duplication, redundancy, etc.).
2. Demonstrates high level SQL and data extraction skills (i.e., Uses pre-defined scripts, changes parameters, GUI query (e.g., MS Access, tools with drag-drop query creation capability, and Excel cubes).
3. Uses standard Intermountain Reporting tools to generate reports for end users that interpret data for others to promote evidence-based decision making.
4. Possesses a fundamental understanding of the domain's data and associated data models and uses it to produce high quality material.
5. Compares data output to ensure data accuracy. Creates basic QA test plans and validates data for accuracy.
6. Responsible to document work / projects per enterprise-wide standards (reports, project tracking, databases, etc.).
7. Understands the appropriate use of indexes, partitions, ability to understand Entity Relationship Diagrams.
8. Uses / analyzes Intermountain data sources (EDW, ORMIS, AS400, Essbase, Risk Management, etc.) to meet local and enterprise needs.
9. Provides consultation, data analysis and project management for clinical and business stakeholders across the organization. Communicates technical / analytical concepts to others.
10. Shares important and relevant information with the team. Proactively offers suggestions, provides resources, volunteers for assignments, and removes barriers to help the team accomplish its goals.
11. Contributes to Intermountain's analyst community by participating in monthly analyst community events such as ASK (Analysts Seeking Knowledge) through presenting, teaching, and mentoring.
Minimum Qualifications
Bachelor's Degree with five years of analytics experience. Degree must be obtained through an accredited institution. Education is verified.
- or -
Master's Degree and three years of analytics experience.
- and -
Demonstrated proficiency and an advanced working knowledge of SQL (structured query language), quality improvement principles, and a solid knowledge of database design principles.
- and -
Demonstrated experience in developing, analyzing, interpreting, and managing a variety of complex data sets.
- and -
Demonstrated capabilities in planning, participating, and managing a variety of complex analytics projects.
- and -
Demonstrated strong proficiency using word processing, spreadsheet, database, internet and e-mail, and scheduling applications.
- and -
Demonstrated experience in a role requiring effective verbal, written, and interpersonal communication skills.
- and -
Solid experience using industry standard BI, statistical, or analytical tools and technologies.
- and -
Demonstrated applied understanding of data visualization design best practices.
Preferred Qualifications
Degree in an analytics-related field such as statistics, mathematics, information systems, computer science, finance, economics, or an MBA with an emphasis in analytics.
- and -
If degree is not in an analytics related field seven years of analytics experience demonstrating proficiency performing the job essentials at this job level.
- and -
Proficiency using statistical methods and tools.
- and -
Proficiency using programming languages and tools.
- and -
Experience presenting to a variety of audiences and coaching leaders, customers and peers on data analysis best practices, trends, tools, and techniques.
- and -
Strong experience with SQL query tuning.
- and -
General experience in healthcare or subject matter expertise in the job area (such as Actuarial, Clinical Programs, Clinical Services, Compliance, Finance/Accounting, Human Resources, Management Engineering, Quality, Revenue Cycle, Select Health / Insurance, Strategic Planning, Costing, Chargemaster, Budgeting, etc.).
Physical Requirements:
Interact with others requiring the employee to verbally communicate information.
- and -
Operate computers and other IT equipment requiring the ability to move fingers and hands.
- and -
See and read computer monitors and documents
- and -
Remain sitting or standing for long periods of time to perform work on a computer, telephone, or other equipment.
- and -
Remain sitting or standing for long periods of time to perform work on a computer, telephone, or other equipment.
- and -
Location:
Key Bank Tower
Work City:
Salt Lake City
Work State:
Utah
Scheduled Weekly Hours:
40
The hourly range for this position is listed below. Actual hourly rate dependent upon experience.
$42.63 - $67.13
We care about your well-being – mind, body, and spirit – which is why we provide our caregivers a generous benefits package that covers a wide range of programs to foster a sustainable culture of wellness that encompasses living healthy, happy, secure, connected, and engaged. Learn more about our comprehensive benefits package (https://intermountainhealthcare.org/careers/working-for-intermountain/employee-benefits/) and our commitment to diversity, equity, and inclusion (https://intermountainhealthcare.org/careers/working-for-intermountain/diversity/) .
Intermountain Healthcare is a Utah-based, not-for-profit system of 33 hospitals (includes "virtual" hospital), a Medical Group with more than 3,800 physicians and advanced practice clinicians at about 385 clinics, a health plans division called SelectHealth, and other health services. Helping people live the healthiest lives possible, Intermountain is widely recognized as a leader in clinical quality improvement and efficient healthcare delivery.
Join our world-class team and embark on a career filled with opportunities, strength, innovation, and fulfillment.
To find out more about us, head to our career site here (https://intermountainhealthcare.org/careers/?utm\_source=Workday&utm\_medium=Redirect&utm\_campaign=CareerHome\_workday) .
Intermountain Healthcare strives to make the application process accessible to all users. If you would like to contact us regarding the accessibility of our website or need assistance completing the application process, please contact 1-800-843-7820 or email recruitment@imail.org . This contact information is for accommodation requests only and cannot be used to inquire about the status of applications.
Intermountain Healthcare is an equal opportunity employer. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability or protected veteran status.
We intentionally work toward an Intermountain Healthcare that reflects our diverse communities and provides culturally competent care, health equity, and a sense of belonging amongst all our caregivers (employees). This is an important part of fulfilling our mission to help people live the healthiest lives possible. The three pillars of our work are talent experience with Intermountain (application, internship, development, etc.), community benefit, and care delivery.
Learn more about diversity at Intermountain, here. (https://intermountainhealthcare.org/careers/working-for-intermountain/diversity/)
Introduce yourself to our Talent Acquisition team and we will get in touch if there is a role that seems like a good match.
Intermountain Healthcare’s PEAK program supports caregivers in the pursuit of their education goals and career aspirations by providing up-front tuition coverage paid directly to the academic institution. The program offers 100+ learning options to choose from, including undergraduate studies, high school diplomas, and professional skills and certificates. Caregivers are eligible to participate in PEAK on day 1 of employment. Learn more. (https://intermountainhealthcare.org/careers/working-for-intermountain/employee-benefits/peak-program/)
The primary intent of this job description is to set a fair and equitable rate of pay for this classification. Only those key duties necessary for proper job evaluation and/or labor market analysis have been included. Other duties may be assigned by the supervisor.
All positions subject to close without notice. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, national origin, disability or protected veteran status. Women, minorities, individuals with disabilities, and veterans are encouraged to apply.
Thanks for your interest in continuing your career with our team

2. Writes more advanced SQL including some query tuning and complex joins (e.g., outer joins on multiple tables). Uses sub-queries and the With Statement as well as more complex functions (e.g., Substr, To_Date, date calculations, etc.).

3. Assists in the identification of data quality (accuracy, completeness, etc.) issues. Assists with the process of database design for assigned projects. As appropriate, trains other individuals and teams in the routine use of data collection, analysis, and reporting and interpretation tools for measuring performance.

4. Demonstrates an understanding of Primary / Foreign Keys, Table / Field Aliases, and Partitions / Indexes to produce high quality material.

5. Provides project management / project leadership as appropriate to drive timelines and deliverables.

6. Trains others on skills and competencies required for previous levels of Data Analyst.

Additional Essentials:

1. Collaborates with corporate and region resources to design, create, test, and implement analytic tools (databases, reports, web applications, dashboards, etc.) that support enterprise / region needs and to improve data collection and reporting strategies (minimize duplication, redundancy, etc.).

2. Demonstrates high level SQL and data extraction skills (i.e., Uses pre-defined scripts, changes parameters, GUI query (e.g., MS Access, tools with drag-drop query creation capability, and Excel cubes).

3. Uses standard Intermountain Reporting tools to generate reports for end users that interpret data for others to promote evidence-based decision making.

4. Possesses a fundamental understanding of the domain's data and associated data models and uses it to produce high quality material.

5. Compares data output to ensure data accuracy. Creates basic QA test plans and validates data for accuracy.

6. Responsible to document work / projects per enterprise-wide standards (reports, project tracking, databases, etc.).

7. Understands the appropriate use of indexes, partitions, ability to understand Entity Relationship Diagrams.

8. Uses / analyzes Intermountain data sources (EDW, ORMIS, AS400, Essbase, Risk Management, etc.) to meet local and enterprise needs.

9. Provides consultation, data analysis and project management for clinical and business stakeholders across the organization. Communicates technical / analytical concepts to others.

10. Shares important and relevant information with the team. Proactively offers suggestions, provides resources, volunteers for assignments, and removes barriers to help the team accomplish its goals.

11. Contributes to Intermountain's analyst community by participating in monthly analyst community events such as ASK (Analysts Seeking Knowledge) through presenting, teaching, and mentoring.
• *Minimum Qualifications**

Bachelor's Degree with five years of analytics experience. Degree must be obtained through an accredited institution. Education is verified.

- or -

Master's Degree and three years of analytics experience.

- and -

Demonstrated proficiency and an advanced working knowledge of SQL (structured query language), quality improvement principles, and a solid knowledge of database design principles.

- and -

Demonstrated experience in developing, analyzing, interpreting, and managing a variety of complex data sets.

- and -

Demonstrated capabilities in planning, participating, and managing a variety of complex analytics projects.

- and -

Demonstrated strong proficiency using word processing, spreadsheet, database, internet and e-mail, and scheduling applications.

Demonstrated experience in a role requiring effective verbal, written, and interpersonal communication skills.

Solid experience using industry standard BI, statistical, or analytical tools and technologies.

title: Data Analyst Technical Senior
description:
Job Description:

Position is 100% remote, however, currently we are unable to consider candidates for remote opportunities in the following states: California, Hawaii, New Jersey, New York, and Washington...

The Senior level Technical Data Analyst position is focused on generating impactful solutions for customers within a defined clinical or business area. The Senior level analyst works within a team and serves as the lead technical support for a system business or clinical domain. Within their team, they mentor junior caregivers providing technical guidance and adherence to best practices. In partnership with the Product Owner, they facilitate regular meetings with customer stakeholders to provide work updates, set project priorities and establish deliverable timelines. They have a deep understanding of the clinical and operating data for the areas they support and consult with Healthcare Data Advisors to ensure the integrity and accuracy of customer data. They drive information insights through data exploration, interpretation, report development and visual storytelling. They are a key member of an Agile Delivery Team comprised of professionals working together to develop technical products focused on enabling Intermountain strategic initiatives and operational targets.

This position is part of a highly skilled, high impact team with deep clinical and technical expertise in leveraging healthcare data to solve real-world problems. Our teams report to senior analytics leaders and work in strong partnership with key business and clinical leaders across all areas of Intermountain Healthcare. This team provides ongoing training, maintenance, monitoring and promotion of data applications and reports to ensure data insights are widely known, accessible, and used to its fullest potential. This position helps develop and deploy world class data analytics at Intermountain Healthcare, one of the nation’s leading health systems. Using the Scaled Agile Framework®, Data Analysts will partner with business and clinical leaders, and data professionals across the organization, supporting our Mission to help people live the healthiest lives possible.

In Brief, the Senior level Technical Data Analyst will demonstrate a deep understanding of the data and operations of the business/clinical areas you support. Partner with Analytic leadership to ensure customer priorities are understood and resourced. Provide a high level of expertise and customer service in order to delight business and clinical customers through innovative and impactful analytic deliverables. Mentor Staff and Associate team members. Detect and facilitate opportunities for intra/inter team collaboration to enhance product work. Contribute technical acumen and thought leadership to the success of your Agile Delivery Team and advance your professional skills though structured and personal learning opportunities

Minimum Qualifications

Must meet one of the following:

Bachelor's degree in an analytics related field such as statistics, mathematics, information systems, computer science, finance, business management, or economics with four years of relevant work experience in a role performing data analysis.

Or

Bachelor’s degree in another area of study with six years of relevant work experience in a role performing data analysis.

Experience without a related degree will be considered if skill set and experience are robust.

Plus:

Demonstration of these skills:

Advanced SQL ability, knowledge of database design, data modeling and standardized data structures

Significant Experience in creating visually appealing, content rich and consumer centric reports and dashboards (i.e. Cognos, Tableau)

Proficiency in using word processing, spreadsheet, internet, e-mail, and scheduling applications

Highly effective verbal, written and interpersonal communication skills

Subject matter expertise in healthcare or related data (Clinical Programs, Clinical Services, Compliance, Quality, Revenue Cycle, Strategic Planning, Population Health, etc.).

Lifelong learner with a creative, collaborative approach.

Temperament to thrive in scaled agile teams (SAFe®) or similar product management practice

Preferred Qualifications

Bachelor's degree in an analytics related field such as statistics, mathematics, information systems, computer science, finance, business management, or economics.

title: Data Analyst II
description:
Data Analyst II

223694BR...

Data Analyst II

US - California - Remote / Field

Job Description

As part of the Thermo Fisher Scientific team, you’ll discover meaningful work that makes a positive impact on a global scale. Join our colleagues in bringing our Mission to life every single day to enable our customers to make the world healthier, cleaner and safer. We provide our global teams with the resources needed to achieve individual career goals while helping to take science a step beyond by developing solutions for some of the world’s toughest challenges, like protecting the environment, making sure our food is safe or helping find cures for cancer.

How will you make an impact?
The Enterprise Services Data Analyst will work closely with business users to collect requirements and build scalable and optimum BI solutions. They are a creative problem solver with a good technical and business background who is able to visualize the hidden insights in data. They will craft, develop and implement solutions that will drive impactful insights for our business and customers across the ES organization.

What will you do?
• Use knowledge of the specific data available, forecasting/analysis methods and visualization capabilities to provide insightful suggestions to business partners
• Analyze data to obtain meaningful business and customer insights
• Participates in business and executive meetings to gather requirements and make recommendations reporting/BI solutions
• Design, build, deliver and maintain world-class reporting for all areas of the business using Power BI
• Assists in the daily support of end-users’ ability to effectively and efficiently utilize the reporting platform
• Supporting development of BI roadmap based on project prioritization and budget
• Collaborating with team to ensure data quality and integrity in data warehouse platforms for BI reporting
• Develop deep understanding of the various business processes, datasets and BI deliverables
• Proactively address scalability and performance issues
• Communicate and collaborate with users to analyze information needs and functional requirements
• Collaborate with developers and domain experts to establish the technical vision and analyze tradeoffs between usability and performance needs

How will you get here?
Education:
• Minimum required education: BS degree or equivalent in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or related field

Experience:
• 3+ years working experience in delivering BI solutions with a strong preference of experience working in the Power BI service
• Experienced with analyzing complex data to obtain insights
• Experience installing, configuring and maintaining BI platforms
• Demonstrable experience in defining and designing KPI metrics
• Excellent knowledge of business processes and standard methodologies
• Knowledge of data warehouse concepts and ETL development
• Experience in SQL and Python preferred but not required

Knowledge, Skills, Abilities:
• Capable of prioritizing multiple projects while still achieving deadlines
• Excellent written and oral communication skills
• Detail-oriented person who is passionate about quality and enthusiastic about new technology
• Highly self-driven, innovative and execution-focused, with a willingness to do "what it takes” to deliver results
• Strategic, intellectually curious thinker with focus on outcomes
• Solid understanding of BI and data warehouse concepts and terminology
• Experience building complex reports in Power BI, Tableau or similar platforms
• Proficiency with O365 Applications including Microsoft Outlook, Word, and Excel

Our Mission is to enable our customers to make the world healthier, cleaner and safer. Watch as our colleagues explain 5 reasons to work with us. As one global team of 100,000 colleagues, we share a common set of values - Integrity, Intensity, Innovation and Involvement - working together to accelerate research, solve complex scientific challenges, drive technological innovation and support patients in need. #StartYourStory at Thermo Fisher Scientific, where diverse experiences, backgrounds and perspectives are valued.

title: Jr. Data Analyst
description:
Job description

Staffigo is in the business of providing IT Consulting Services to clients in various industries in the United States - Healthcare (Payer, Providers & Clearinghouses), Finance & Banking, Retail & eCommerce. We are currently seeking exceptional entry-level talent for the below role...

Responsibilities:
• Create, validate and send daily, weekly, and monthly management reports to clients.
• Assistance with requests for non-standard reports and analysis for clients.
• Support management reporting by maintaining hierarchy information.
• Research and answer client's questions.
• Perform business-to-system analysis and troubleshooting analysis of complex management reports and business problems with guidance.
• In the report, development lifecycle support impact analysis and project requirements definition.
• Transform client needs into functional requirements. With guidance, collect, analyze and document business requirements for project proposals including but not limited to process and data flow, user interface, security, and reporting requirements.
• Together with managers and/or senior analysts, participate in cross-functional meetings where customers are interviewed to understand customer needs and identify problems and solutions. appropriate solutions, develop specifications, analyze and document business processes, validate testing processes, and train the user community.
• Support teamwork and get internal and external client feedback on processes, procedures, and technology.

Qualifications:
• Master’s degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or any related field of study.
• No travel; no telecommuting. Job duties are project-based and performed on long-term assignments at various unanticipated sites within the U.S. which may require relocation at the end of each project.
• Advanced Excel skills (pivot tables, v-lookups, charts).
• Experience using the relational database system, Oracle preferred.
• Excellent oral and written communication skills.
• Understanding of software development life cycle.
• Must know how to use Power BI or Tableau.
• Experience with hands-on and manual data tasks
• Excellent analytical skills.
• Ability to handle multiple projects under tight deadlines.
• Attention to detail and ability to follow instructions and written processes to deliver requirements.

-Support Project Manager in strategic process-based roadmap development using tools and analytical features to support existing processes.
-Interpreting large volumes of data using models and data visualization.

Monitors tasks to meet contractual/project requirements for assigned programs

-Strong computer skills with advanced knowledge of Microsoft applications
-Team player with the ability to work cross functionally with different levels of the organization
-Ability to independently manage daily projects and tasks assigned by management
-Ability to function in a fast-paced, rapidly changing environment
-Passion for making concrete business impact

title: Data Analyst (WGU Academy)
description:
If you’re passionate about building a better future for individuals, communities, and our country—and you’re committed to working hard to play your part in building that future—consider WGU as the next step in your career.

Driven by a mission to expand access to higher education through online, competency-based degree programs, WGU is also committed to being a great place to work for a diverse... workforce of student-focused professionals. The university has pioneered a new way to learn in the 21st century, one that has received praise from academic, industry, government, and media leaders. Whatever your role, working for WGU gives you a part to play in helping students graduate, creating a better tomorrow for themselves and their families.

Current WGU employees should submit an internal application before 12/20/2022 to be considered.

Who is WGU Academy?

At WGU Academy, we work collaboratively to dramatically impact college and workforce readiness efforts on a large scale. Our primary mission is to develop and deliver new solutions for college and career readiness to tens of thousands, even hundreds of thousands, of individuals who otherwise would not be prepared for regular enrollment at WGU or at other institutions of Higher Education.

This is a fully benefited, remote position that can be located anywhere in the 48 US States.

Why consider us?
• Fully remote position where you’ll make a difference in a mission driven environment.
• Equipment provided: Choice of Mac or PC laptop
• Comprehensive and affordable benefits (including mental health benefits, and generous PTO) plus 403b matches and contributions where we put money into your retirement account, even if you’re not contributing.
• 75% employee tuition discount available at WGU for yourself, and 50% discount for qualifying family members.
• Innovative, fun, and enriching team environment where are you valued, given credit where its due, and recognized for your contributions.
• Collaborative and cross functional team, where good communication is prioritized.

What will you be doing?

WGU Academy uses a data and research-driven, evidence-based approach to learning success and the organization has a healthy respect for analytics and data in general.

As a Data Analyst with WGU Academy, you’ll work on real-world problems that identify levels of learner success and most importantly use data to inform the building of interventions that help struggling learners reach their goals. This includes a deep analysis of learner profiles, learner learning patterns, academic and career outcomes, and course and learning resource quality. You’ll answer questions posed by others, but also be expected and encouraged to and answer your own questions. As a thought leader for analytics, you’ll interact with researchers, academic leaders, curriculum design experts, and other data analysts across the organization to continuously analyze and improve course and program performance and learner outcomes.

Who will you be helping?

Findings about learners and their experiences are used immediately and lead to direct, actionable interventions and changes to help current and future learners succeed. Your data analysis will shape learning experiences for individual learners who have traditionally been underserved in Higher Education.

Who are you?

You’re inquisitive and have the desire to innovate and test ideas in an environment where iteration is encouraged and expected. You enjoy working at a fast pace on projects that have clear-cut deadline and objectives and follow a 2-3 week sprint cycle. You love working with data and are excited about creating and improving learning experiences for our learners.

How is success measured?

We’ve built out a training plan so you can familiarize with data, gain a solid understanding of the metrics and status quo before jumping into creating descriptive analysis, building out automated calculations. From here you’ll jump into inferential statistics, and, visualization build outs.

Once you’re up to speed with our data and processes, success will be measured against the number of deliverables, the speed of generation, and quality of your findings.

Essential Functions and Responsibilities:

Working with other analysts and researchers in a sprint fashion, you’ll be expected to expertly handle multiple projects simultaneously, each at different stages of the analytics cycle. You’ll be cleaning data, performing manipulation and analysis, creating reports and dashboards for presentation; attending a handful of meetings, and working on projects that align to interests and key priorities for the organization. There will be opportunity to build out systems, further data refinement, automate jobs, and create automated dashboards that will replace manual processes.
• Defines analytic projects in a way that delivers business value to WGU Academy
• Identifies needs and creates novel analytic projects (rather than simply responding to requests)
• Analyzes and interprets diverse sets of educational data using a variety of statistical methods (e.g., t-tests, regression, natural language processing, thematic analysis, structural equation modeling, Chi-square, factor analysis, hierarchical/multi-level modeling)
• Uses SQL, Python, R, or Scala to clean, manipulate, and transform data for analysis
• Reports, explains, and presents statistical analyses to the most senior leadership teams using graphs, charts, and tables
• Designs and maintains Tableau dashboards
• Applies understanding of learning science to develop methods for measuring learning and engagement
• Uses understanding of data collection to design and implement new methods of measurement
• Stays informed of emerging trends in learning science, learning analytics, and data science
• Clearly communicates with users to assess needs and requirements for data products
• Pitches value of potential data products using functioning proofs-of-concept
• Works across academic colleges and programs to provide valuable data-informed insights on trends of performance metrics

What you’ll bring:
• Strong written, oral, presentation, and interpersonal skills, including the ability to explain the significance of data and trends to stakeholders
• Ability to manage multiple, competing tasks independently while working in a team environment
• Ability to provide mentoring to more junior team members
• Work with outside vendors and internal teams to improve data availability and quality
• Ability to use SQL, R, Python, or SAS to run descriptive, inferential, multivariate, and other statistical analyses
• Ability to create data dashboards and visuals using tools like Tableau and Databricks
• Ability to create datasets for analysis & reporting using SQL, Python, R, or Scala.
• Ability to explain analysis results to non-technical audience
• Ability to manage multiple ongoing data projects

Qualifications

Minimum Qualifications:
• Bachelor’s degree required
• 2 years of professional data analysis experience
• Proficient in Microsoft Excel, Tableau, and Power BI
• Proficient in building relational database queries using programming languages like SQL, Spark SQL, R, Python, or Scala

Preferred Qualifications:
• Master’s Degree
• Familiarity with Databricks, Salesforce

Disclaimers:

WGU Academy, Inc is an affiliated non-profit entity of 501c(3) Corporation of Western Governors University

title: PQI Data Analyst
description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

SCO Family of Services is an accredited agency with more than 80 programs and more than 100 facilities located across New York State. The agency's programs are regulated by state and local government agencies such as the Department of Health, Office of Mental Health, Education Department, Office of Children and Family Services, and Office for People with Developmental... Disabilities; we also adhere to Federal, State, and local licensing, regulatory and accreditation standards.

Salary: 60K-65K commensurate with experience.

At SCO Family of Services, we embrace a philosophy and a series of techniques for continuous quality improvement (CQI) to improve overall organizational performance and for meeting standards that promote quality outcomes in public health and human services for the populations we cover. At every step, data and analytics is the driving force of CQI and evidence-based decision making. In this role, you will be part of a team that improves quality and performance various, multi-disciplinary settings. General responsibilities:
• Design, maintain, and improve dynamic data systems and databases by fixing coding errors and addressing other data-related problems.
• Mine data from primary and secondary sources, and refine data and layouts as needed.
• Use tools to conduct statistical analyses on big data sets, attending to trends and patterns that could be valuable for diagnostic and predictive analytics.
• Prepare reports for executive leadership that effectively communicate trends, patterns, and predictions using relevant data.
• Collaborate with organizational leaders to identify opportunities for process improvements, recommend system modifications, and develop policies for data governance.
• Create appropriate documentation that allows stakeholders to understand the steps of the data analysis process and duplicate or replicate the analysis if necessary.
• Assist with the development and implementation of various CQI initiatives and Accreditations.
• Collaborate with colleagues from outside agencies; work with stakeholders to assess potential risks.
• Analyze existing tools and databases and provide software solution recommendations.
• Methodologically process and manage large scale data sets and relational databases
• Effectively communicate findings, from transformed data and translated business requirements, into terms appropriate for various audiences
• Work independently and in collaboration with a wide variety of constituents.
• Take initiative to troubleshoot and see tasks through to completion
• Assists and supports quarterly and annual CQI reporting as well as accreditation/re-accreditation activities, as well as for other analytical and technical tasks, upon request.

Additional responsibilities into providing technical assistance/expertise:
• Development and validation of performance and quality measures and key performance indicators (KPIs): supports analytical and technical activities relating administrative elements, including understanding the departmental and programmatic context; collects, analyzes, and organizes data from administrative departments and programs to generate regular reports; monitoring and evaluation of data pertaining to incidents, accidents, and grievances by developing and updating tools for tracking/reconciliation; monitors data quality to ensure the submission and validation of data is complete and timely.
• Data analysis and reporting: participate in continual improvement of data collection and reporting while ensuring assigned data steps are completed; automate analytic processes/data flows; interprets and presents results of completed analyses and can intelligently articulate/discuss the methodologies used; support evidence-based decision-making by making recommendations to improve program performance and increase proactive program management.
• Involved with committees and various interdisciplinary meetings and reviews: schedules and leads interdisciplinary Program and Administrative KPI review meetings and generates/distributes these meetings’ materials; for the organization’s Board, Executive Council, and Cabinet-level Committees, produces and presents meeting materials/reports; other meetings/generally, participates in internal and external meetings, as needed.

QUALIFICATIONS:

Education & Experience
• Degree in an analytical, technical, or scientific field (e.g., data science, computer science, bioinformatics, biostatistics, epidemiology, public health, public administration, etc.). Master’s or doctoral degree preferred.
• A minimum of 3-5 years of experience, preferably in public sector settings, with proficiency in at least some of the following:

o Relational database concepts/query tools/electronic data capture (e.g., SQL, Visual Basic, REDCap, Excel, Forms, etc.)

o Business intelligence and visualization tools (e.g., Power BI, Tableau, Excel, , or other Interactive and dynamic Dashboards/Widgets.)

o Presentation tools (e.g., MS Word, PowerPoint, etc.)

o Statistical analysis tools (SAS, R, SPSS, etc.)

o Experience with standard analytic methodologies and techniques (e.g., trending, benchmark comparisons, etc.) and complex task management (including work breakdown structures/project management tools such as Asana, Smartsheet etc.)

o Ability to communicate complex concepts orally and in various electronic/written formats

o Supports Performance and Quality initiatives, projects, and tasks, as needed.

RELATIONSHIP WITH OTHERS:

1. Must be a team player and able to interact with the program’s leadership, supervisory and line staff, as well as with the agency Vice Presidents for both Program and Performance and Quality and the Agency’s Central PQ staff, understanding chains of command.

2. Have a strong sensitivity to cultural differences to work well with staff, persons and families served and complete tasks as assigned.

3. Possess a strong belief in people’s ability to grow and change; forge a mutually respectful partnership with staff at all levels.

4. Ability to set limits, maintain role, work collaboratively and respectfully to intervene appropriately.

5. Demonstrate commitment to empower program management and staff through training and problem-solving in a strength-based environment.

WORKING CONDITIONS:

1. Work remotely (home office).

2. Collaborative meetings via Zoom/MS Teams

Statement

SCO Family of Services is committed to ensuring the safety of our clients. All staff are screened and trained. Any inappropriate interactions with clients are taken seriously. We will fully cooperate with authorities in any case of abuse.

title: Senior Data Analyst - Remote US
description:
About Seamless

Seamless delivers the world’s best sales leads. Through our product, we help sales teams maximize revenue, increase sales, and easily acquire their total addressable market using artificial intelligence; by development of a robust real-time contact and company search engine as well as a suite of technically-advanced tools to support sales and lead generation. We have been... recognized as one of Ohio’s fastest growing companies and have been recently ranked No. 7 in LinkedIn's Top 50 Startups of 2022, featured in Forbes as #1 Software company in Ohio in 2022, and on G2’s “Top 100 Highest Satisfaction Products for 2022” list!

The Opportunity

The Senior Data Analyst will be a key member of the Engineering Product and Development Team reporting to the VP of Product. This individual will help us better interpret our robust datasets to maximize our internal operations, as well as provide data-driven decisions for product growth. The Senior Data Analyst will also help use data for elevating important executive insights, optimizing our AI/ML logic, and improving overall data coverage and accuracy. This individual will work with a wide range of datasets and collaborate across the various internal business verticals at Seamless.

Responsibilities:
• Manage and execute data analysis initiatives to drive product updates, enhancements and fixes.
• Identify key internal performance metrics and create automated reporting/analysis for measuring success.
• Work closely with our data analytics platform SME (Product Ops) to maintain and optimize those platforms, including Gainsight (CX and PX), Segment, Hotjar, and Google Analytics.
• Work with Business Intelligence software, such as Tableau.
• Evaluate and assist in decision making for any new analytics and product data platforms to enhance our analytics tech stack.
• Manage development of data resources, gather requirements, organize sources, and support tagging and measurement surrounding product launches.
• Build and scale our product analytics team, with opportunities to lead and manage the team including owning data best practices and our overall data taxonomy.

Experience and Skills:
• Bachelor’s degree in Analytics, Mathematics/Statistics, Computer Science or related field or equivalent professional experience required.
• 4+ years of experience in Data Analytics, with an interest in sales and sales-enablement tools.
• Experience working in software and digital products.
• Fluency in Structured Query Language (PostgresSQL, MySQL, MSSQL, Presto, etc.) and working with large relational databases.
• Experience leveraging Data Visualization Tools such as Tableau, Qlik or PowerBI for creating dashboard analytics.
• Top notch organizational skills and ability to work within processes, as well as develop and optimize processes.
• Thorough attention to detail and able to generate insights from large datasets.
• Strong verbal and written communication skills.
• Ability to work independently, manage multiple priorities / projects and pivot between responsibilities in a fast-paced, high-growth environment.
• Ability to collaborate with team members and execute on project plans that require input from others on the team.
• Exemplary personal and professional integrity and business ethics.
• Strong technical understanding and experience implementing tagging and strategy for software and/or online product analytics. Analytics certifications are a plus.
• Experience with our current analytics stack is a plus: Google Analytics, Tableau, Segment, Gainsight, Hotjar (or similar platforms)
• Practical understanding of statistical analysis methods a plus: Anomaly Detection, Regression, Segmentation/Clustering, etc.
• Familiarity with AWS Cloud Services a plus

Role Details / Example Projects:

This role will entail working with teams throughout the company and with various leaders in each department. This includes leading as well as supporting items such as the following:
• Enhancing product data through improvement in our data algorithms for things like data accuracy, recommendations and more.
• Optimizing list building processes and working with our data team to develop target lists for sales and marketing.
• Evaluating and improving sales conversion metrics through data analysis.
• Identifying new marketing opportunities through data analysis.
• Developing and optimizing ROI reports for internal use as well as end-users.
• Supporting development and optimization of user dashboards for metrics analysis.
• Evaluating and improvement core SaaS business KPIs such as churn, conversion rates and renewal rates,
• Evaluating and optimizing pricing strategies for the product and business,
• Evaluating product metrics to optimize product workflows and new feature opportunities.
• And more...

Culture

We have an amazing culture and work environment that anyone would want to be a part of. We encourage a culture of positivity. We thrive off of continuous feedback and do whatever it takes to help our team and customers be successful. You will grow as an individual, professionally, and be able to see and feel the impact you are making to the growth of Seamless every day. With a purpose to positively impact a billion people and help the economy generate a trillion dollars in growth, our mission here at Seamless.AI is to help every professional globally create new relationships and opportunities, faster than ever before using the power of AI!

Perks and Benefits

• Great Medical, dental, and vision benefits (short-term disability & and term life insurance also available)

• Several Paid Holidays + Paid Time Off (PTO) Days + Corporate Philanthropy days

• Option to allocate pre-tax dollars to 401K and have company match (after working for 1 year)

• Eligible to participate in our "Equity for All" plan with stock options, becoming a partial owner of Seamless.AI!

• Summer Fridays (2pm dismissal on Fridays in the summer), Free Headspace subscription, and more!

Seamless.AI has been delivering the world's best sales leads since 2015. Our product is the first real time, B2B search engine helping sales teams maximize revenue, increase sales, and easily acquire their total addressable market using artificial intelligence. We have been recognized as one of Ohio’s fastest growing companies and won 2020 Best Places to Work and LinkedIn’s Top 50 Tech Startups 2020. We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. title: Senior Business Data Analyst
description:
Job Purpose

The Sr. Business Data Specialist is responsible for Data Quality and Data Integrity in order to support Business Data for use in business intelligence/decisions. Major focus areas will be in Customer Data, Product Data, Supplier Data and the classification and standardization of that data. This may also include customers' assets and support contracts in our asset/contract management... tool.

Data aspects include its accuracy, accessibility, consistency, completeness, and updating. Maintains integrity of this data through periodic housekeeping efforts. Proactively manages this process on a regular schedule. Identifies, reviews, and fixes data inconsistencies.

Uses data quality monitoring to communicate errors in data back to operational team members. Works to create and submit new policies or standards for ensuring appropriate data entry, usage, and controls.

Establishes, coordinates and maintains solid communication with the sales teams and sales support teams while updating data records as needed in keeping with established policies and procedures. Reviews and actions any OEM or supplier hardware, software, and renewal notifications.

Essential Functions

SPECIFIC TO MASTER DATA MANAGEMENT:
• Responsible for the standardization and classification of the product data that goes into our Order Management system. Additionally, responsible for ensuring those classifications that relate to financial reporting (tax codes, recycle codes, and category codes) are properly established. Also, works with 3rd party services such as cNET's Product Standardization service to enhance our data.
• Responsible for the standardization and classification of the customer data in all of the appropriate systems (OQS, ChangePoint, Dynamics, OneSource, etc.). Responsible for ensuring that those classifications that relate to financial reporting (Customer Classification) are properly set based on information available through the customer's website and various business portals on the internet. Ensure that any hierarchical relationships are linked at the time of customer set-up, and any duplicate information is properly merged.
• Responsible for maintaining OnX Governance Documentation
• Responsible for the standardization and classification of our supplier/vendor information in all of the appropriate systems (OQS, ChangePoint, Dynamics, etc.). Ensure that any hierarchical relationships are linked at the time of supplier set-up, and any duplicate information is properly merged.

SPECIFIC TO RENEWALS DATA MANAGEMENT:
• Audit specific data fields at the end of every month for sales out information that is required to populate our customer asset and contract management tool. Work with appropriate departments to update any missing or incorrect data. Search internal systems, supplier systems, and/or OEM systems to identify accurate information to update any missing or incorrect data.
• Provide complete and accurate monthly sales out data in a template to populate our customer asset and contract management tool. Reconciles any records that were not able to be validated in the asset/contract tool until they are accurate and able to be loaded correctly.
• Identify all expiring contracts approximately 120 days in advance of expiration by utilizing internal tools, OEM tools, and/or supplier tools and provide complete and accurate expiration reports to specified users in the organizations.
• Review the information for each expiring contract to ensure that the required data elements are complete and accurate. Update any missing or incorrect data in the appropriate internal systems, supplier systems, and/or OEM systems so that the information is ready to be used in the quote process starting 90 days in advance of contract expiration.
• Reconcile any data variances reported by the customer, internal departments, sales teams, suppliers, or OEMs in a timely manner to preempt any escalations.

SPECIFIC TO LOB ASSET DATA MANAGEMENT:
• Manage data integrity across the timeline of a specific bill of material and/or project roll out
• Reconcile historical transactions
• Synchronize customer maintained installation records
• Collaborate with OEMs to enhance data exchange process to improve

GENERAL RESPONSIBILITIES
• Assist internal customers, suppliers, and OEMs with creating and maintaining reports as needed
• Work with various vendors and tools to further enhance our system and available business data to help our leaders make better decisions
• Create and submit new policies or standards for ensuring appropriate data entry, usage, and controls
• Adhere to data governance standard operating procedures
• Maintain a high level of knowledge regarding systems and tools in order to act as a subject matter expert regarding functionality, navigation, structure, data, and business application
• Other duties as assigned

Experience
• 3 to 5 years of general work experience

Education
• Four years of College resulting in a Bachelor's Degree or equivalent

Special Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities
• Excellent communication skills and interpersonal skills
• Competency in Microsoft Office Applications (Outlook, Excel, Word, PowerPoint, etc.)
• Excel Level 2 competence
• Demonstrates good organizational and detail-oriented skills
• Demonstrates effective time management, multi-tasking, and self-starter attributes
• Proven ability to interact and cooperate with employees in all departments
• Strong business acumen
• Upholds confidentiality

Supervisory Responsibilities

No Supervisory Responsibility

title: Data Quality Analyst I - Remote
description:
ULTRA MOBILE is seeking a talented Data Quality Analyst I to join the Enterprise Information Management ! Individual reports to Principal Data Quality Analyst. Role is remote - must reside in the United States.

About The Role...

The Data Quality Analyst I role within the Enterprise Information Management organization will be instrumental in supporting the implementation of data quality monitoring and operations, enabling data driven decisions and ensuring data quality is deployed as a value-add service. As an ambassador and data quality champion, you will have an opportunity to interact with both technical and business partners. Technical capabilities aside, if you’re a mission-driven strategic thinker with strong communications, excellent analytical skills, creative, who can work effectively both independently and as part of a team, then you’ll be a perfect fit for our team.

Your usual day of awesomeness includes:
• Analyze & profile data to assess quality variances from data standards while working with technical & business stakeholders to ensure continuous process improvement.
• Assess operational processes to ensure (data profiling/metadata/lineage) are maintained, updated, and automated processes are developed/enhanced.
• Develop data quality monitoring against operational data sources and data lake/warehouse utilizing data quality tools to ensure adherence to standards with continuous improvement goals.
• Develop data quality scorecards according to data quality dimensions & by appropriate data domain to baseline and monitor for improvement goals.
• Translate business requirements to triage data quality issues and provide recommendations/solutions to meet the true business needs.
• Work with technical & business stakeholders to ensure proactive and continuous process improvement.
• Perform follow-up actions related to findings & ensure relevant parties understand data quality gaps and close them accordingly.
• Develop a thorough understanding of products and services, business processes, current/historical data, and system environments.

What You Bring
• Bachelor's degree in computer science, information management, or related field.
• 3+ years in a data quality or data management roles.
• 3+ years of experience in a business/data analyst or BI/reporting roles.
• 3+ Experience tracing lineage and building data quality monitoring rules leveraging Collibra Data Quality, Collibra DIC, or similar data governance/data quality tools.
• Experienced in multiple relevant topics such as data warehousing, information design, analytics, data science, and knowledge management.
• Experience in querying databases using SQL.
• Experienced building reporting/dashboards/scorecards leveraging BI/Reporting Tools (Looker, Tableau) or other data visualization software.

Exos provides certified coaches, therapists, dieticians, psychologists, and instructors for over 400 locations globally, ranging from corporate sites and community programs to military and athlete training centers. THE ROLE

The Reporting Data Analyst on the Exos Service Delivery team will be a data specialist who contributes to operational improvement and efficiency by gathering and analyzing data, preparing reports, and introducing process improvements throughout the reporting process for a large, global client.

The ideal candidate has excellent analytical and technical skills, as well as a keen ability to determine specifications and standards for business reporting and maintaining data integrity. The Reporting Data Analyst will leverage their knowledge, problem solving skills, and passion about analytics to inform the evolution of our digital and on-site experiences and keep our operations running as efficiently as possible.

• Collaborate: Work with executive stakeholders and program management to identify and create metrics and KPIs that enable leaders to manage their areas.

Exos strives to create a workplace culture that prioritizes health, wellness and recovery. We believe that the concepts of happiness and productivity are not mutually exclusive. title: Data Analyst
description:
Clutter is a technology & logistics company based in Los Angeles. We are actively disrupting the $60B/year self-storage and moving industries with our end-to-end supply chain and proprietary technology platform. We offer convenient and tech-enabled Smart Storage and Moving solutions to tens of thousands of customers in 20 states across the US, with more markets being added every year. We’re a... As Clutter continues to grow, we are investing in building out our data function to support critical decision making across the organization. This role is a key component of that investment. The key function of this role will be to build data and reporting solutions, with a focus on SQL coding and dashboard building.
